quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  10,100,"And it is not for a soul [i.e., anyone] to believe except by permission of Allāh, and He will place defilement{1} upon those who will not use reason.",1:[Among its meanings are filth, wrath, punishment, disbelief, confusion and error.]
  10,101,"Say, "
  10,102,"So do they wait except for like [what occurred in] the days of those who passed on before them? Say, "
  11,67,"And the shriek{1} seized those who had wronged, and they became within their homes [corpses] fallen prone",1:[A piercing cry or blast from the sky.]
  11,68,"As if they had never prospered therein. Unquestionably, Thamūd denied their Lord; then, away with Thamūd."
  11,69,"And certainly did Our messengers [i.e., angels] come to Abraham with good tidings; they said, "
  12,28,"So when he [i.e., her husband] saw his shirt torn from the back, he said, "
  12,29,"Joseph, ignore this.{1} And, [my wife], ask forgiveness for your sin. Indeed, you were of the sinful.",1:[i.e., conceal it and act as if it had not taken place.]
